  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: git_branch=devel git_tag=v2021.10.03-1315-g50873a5b1-dirty git_commit= 50873a5b1d163924ec7826886c9a9e8b7275e7df\r\n\r\nOS & Version:Linux\r\n\r\nI am running erigon with `--port 30305` , along with geth (on port 30303) . I use erigons RPC daemon in a different port than 8545.\r\nAfter upgrading to latest devel I noticed the http api started by default\r\n\r\n````\r\n[INFO] HTTP endpoint opened for Engine API      url=localhost:8551 ws=false\r\n[INFO] HTTP endpoint opened                     url=localhost:8545 ws=false ws.compression=true grpc=false\r\n````\r\n\r\nSo I went ahead and added `--http false` since I don't need the build in api.\r\n\r\nErigon started complaining, \r\n\r\n````\r\n[INFO] HTTP endpoint opened for Engine API      url=localhost:8551 ws=false\r\n[INFO] HTTP endpoint opened                     url=localhost:8545 ws=false ws.compression=true grpc=false\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=PeerEvents err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvUploadMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvUploadHeadersMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[INFO] [Snapshots] Fetching torrent files metadata\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=PeerEvents err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvUploadMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvUploadHeadersMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[INFO] New txs subscriber joined\r\n[INFO] new subscription to newHeaders established\r\n[INFO] [Snapshots] Stat                         blocks=13999999 segments=14499999 indices=13999999 alloc=2.0GB sys=3.4GB\r\n[INFO] [1/16 Headers] Waiting for headers...    from=14981360\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=PeerEvents err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvUploadMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvUploadHeadersMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=RecvMessage err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n[WARN] Status error, sentry not ready yet       stream=PeerEvents err=\"could not start server: listen tcp :30303: bind: address already in use\"\r\n````\r\n\r\nSo how do I disable it without causing problems?\r\n",
